title: What To Say When You Talk To Your Self
author: Shad Helmstetter
review: I thought it was gonna be like yea, it's another one that's gonna be boring. The content is actually more eye-opening for me and I didn't expect myself to learn so much from this book. It talks about the different levels show how you view yourself currently.

title: Head First Design Patterns
author: Eric Freeman
review: I was bored on the train when I encountered this book. I've learned many patterns from this book in an interesting way. Definitely recommend this one.

title: The 10X Rule: The Only Difference Between Success and Failure
author: Grant Cardone
review: This book inspired me to "Level UP" myself. The book itself was valuable to me, but the author is not a great influencer in my opinion. He might be a great property saleman, but I don't agree with the way he took money from his followers. The book itself though, definitely brings value to me as a person.

title: Soft Skills: The Software Developer's Life Manual
author: John Sonmez
review: This is the first book that made me realized that software developer is a JOB. To be richer, the book teaches you how to use your programming skills to the fullest such as creating a blog or make instructing videos on how to program. Show the world what you know. Then it also briefly mention about investing on houses and stock.
